  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The `debug_*` series trace operations record the revert reasons when a method call reverts.  However the `trace_*` series do not.  When a call fails I would like the reason to show up in the vmTrace at the operation that made the call and in the flat trace.  When a precompiled call returns a revert reason that also should be included as a trace, even though precompiled calls are not normally in the vmTrace.",
